form.text: Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements
Dollar amounts are in thousands of Canadian dollars (except share and per share amounts)
The investment property segment defined as Other consists of one commercial property of which the Company has a 50% ownership. The
property has a fair value of $2.2 million (December 31, 2012 ‑ $2.1 million).
IPUC includes land held for future development, which is recorded at a fair value of $2.8 million (December 31, 2012 ‑ $5.2 million) and
properties under construction of $21.6 million (December 31, 2012 ‑ $52.7 million). Fair value cannot be reliably determined for properties
under construction as the projects are in the early stages of development and therefore IPUC is recorded at cost.
